Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
change_IB_cell_site_name(25.10)                change_IB_cell_site_name(25.10)

Name
       change_IB_cell_site_name - Change sites for the cells whose site defin-
       itions do not match the site definitions used by Innovus

Syntax
       change_IB_cell_site_name

       [-help]

       [-NF <site_name>]

       [-NNF <site_name>]

       [-PF <site_name>]

       [-PPF <site_name>]

       [-new <site_name>]

       [-original <site_name>]

       [-vertical]

       Change sites for the cells whose site definitions do not match the site
       definitions  used  by  Innovus.  This  is  applicable only for specific
       nodes.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each change_IB_cell_site_name parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man change_IB_cell_site_name

       -NF <site_name>
              Specifies the site name of the N-filler cell.

       -NNF <site_name>
              Specifies site name of NN-filler cell.

       -PF <site_name>
              Specifies the site name of the P-filler cell.

       -PPF <site_name>
              Specifies site name of PP-filler cell.

       -new <site_name>
              Specifies the new site name of the IB cell

       -original <site_name>
              Specifies the original site name of the IB cell.

       -vertical
              Is IB transform.

